Shoutout to @alaskaair ! 
“We are proud to be the first airline to join the Historically Black Colleges and Universities (HBCU) Partnership Challenge. It is an effort put forth by the bipartisan Congressional HBCU Caucus to promote greater engagement and support between private companies and HBCUs.
 
We recently established commitments and specific goals to increase BIPOC representation in leadership, continue to cultivate an inclusive culture, and to lead publicly by supporting education on the path to equity. Learn more at the link in our bio.”

node.text:
Just a reminder that whatever you are going through in life , know that your life can change in a matter of seconds, literally!! 

Do you all remember when college student Anok Yai was spotted in 2017 at Howard University’s homecoming from a photo @thesunk took of her? She has come along way since that photo including magazine covers, modeling agency, and pictured on the right, at the Met Gala yesterday 

What a message from @historicallyblacksince ! 🔥

Meet #Yardrunners 2021: former student-athletes turned pharmacists, entertainers, engineers, entrepreneurs, and the world’s next leaders coming out of Historically Black Colleges and Universities.👏🏾 Always determined to shine, even in the face of success or adversity, these individuals have redefined what it means to be a student athlete.🌟

Head to our 🔗 in bio to shop their Nike Blazer looks. For those in the US, learn more about their stories through the Nike app. #HBCU
